[Student "S"]
{Because SOUTH holds a 4-card Major suit, (\Hs), he starts his 
responses with Stayman.

NORTH denies holding any 4-card Major suit so SOUTH gives up on \Hs. 
He next bids \Ss, showing five of them. He jumps to 3\S, giving NORTH the choice 
between 4\S or 3NT.

With three trumps NORTH chooses 4\S.}

